				<h2> What is Ergonomics? </h2>
				<p>Anyone who works at a desk or computer would benefit from knowing about <i>Ergonomics</i>.</p>
				<div>
					<h3>Origin</h3>
					<p> The Oxford Dictionary defines Ergonomics as: </p>
					<blockquote cite="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/us/definition/english/ergonomics">
						"<i>noun</i> :the study of working conditions, especially the design of equipment and furniture, in order to help people work more efficiently.<br><br>
						from Greek <i>ergon</i> ‘work’+ <i>nemein</i> 'to manage' "
					</blockquote>
				</div>
				
				<div>
					<h3>So what is it?</h3>
					<p>So <i>Ergonomics</i> has to do with, <b> how to manage <em> how one works.</em></b> The science of making your work enviroment more comfortable.</p>
					<details>
						<summary>A Simple Guide to Ergonomics</summary>
